"""Standalone TEOS-10 OHC/TCHP demo for one hardcoded Argo vs RTOFS pair.

This script is intentionally independent of the larger pairing pipeline. It uses
one real collocated pair copied into this file as literal arrays:

- Argo GDAC cast: aoml/4903240/profiles/D4903240_391.nc
- Pair date: 20240928
- Argo profile coordinates: (22.20590, -96.03742)
- Matched RTOFS grid cell: (22.22104, -96.00000)

Why this is useful:
- it gives a minimal reproducible TEOS-10 example
- it can be run by itself without downloading anything
- it shows exactly how we compute OHC/TCHP for one observed profile and one model column

Temporal window note
--------------------
For a strict one-Argo-vs-one-RTOFS comparison, the cleanest choice is same-day or
very-near-time matching, ideally within roughly +/-6 to 24 hours.

A full week can still be useful, but it changes the meaning:
- good for context, support, or sensitivity testing
- not as clean for a one-to-one equivalence claim

So the normal hierarchy is:
- best matchup: same day, nearest model cycle / analysis time
- acceptable sensitivity window: +/-24 h
- contextual window: up to 7 days, but then call it a neighborhood/time-window comparison
  rather than a strict collocation
"""
